About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Title: The Darien Gap üåç The Most Dangerous Places on Earth
Description:
Did you know it‚Äôs impossible to drive from North America to South America by road? üåé The Darien Gap, a 160 km stretch of dense jungle, swamps, and mountains, is the reason why üå≥. This dangerous area blocks the Pan-American Highway, making road construction here nearly impossible and extremely expensive üí∏. The terrain is harsh, with extreme humidity and constant rainfall, but that‚Äôs not the only danger. The Darien Gap is also a lawless zone, home to smugglers, criminals, and armed gangs, making it one of the most treacherous places on Earth üíÄ. Despite this, thousands of migrants attempt to cross these impassable jungles every year in search of a better life, but the risks are immense. Many never reach their destination, lost to the wild or falling victim to the lawlessness that reigns in this region. The Darien Gap remains an impenetrable barrier between North and South America, cutting off what could be the world‚Äôs longest continuous road üö´.

Title: This tiny car shocked me!
Description:
Change your car with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Change-Your-Car-0111

This is the Hyundai Inster!

It‚Äôs an all-new compact electric car that‚Äôs meant to rival similar small EVs like the Citroen EC3! It looks super quirky, but is it more style over substance? Mat‚Äôs about to find out. 

When it comes to the design, the Inster certainly looks unique! Up front there‚Äôs a distinctive design with some of the wildest hazard lights we‚Äôve seen on any car. Along the side, the cuteness & boxy design is turned up to 10, and we think it looks pretty smart with the roof bars added. Unfortunately, though, these aren‚Äôt available on the entry-level car! Around the back, there‚Äôs a unique tail light design, and when the brake is applied they become some of the brightest rear lights we‚Äôve ever seen!

The interior has a 1990s vibe, with quite a bit of plastic throughout the cabin. However, there‚Äôs still quite a lot of stand-out and impressive tech! There‚Äôs a big infotainment screen and a digital dial display. The latter even throws up camera displays when the indicators are used. The whole interior is fairly well-built, and the two-tone effect on the seats is pretty nice. The rear seats also come with lots of adjustment - pretty impressive for such a small car!

There are two battery and motor combinations available. The first is the standard range, which has a single motor that delivers 97hp and a claimed range of 203 miles, while there‚Äôs also a Long Range available. This also has a single motor, but it can put down 115hp and has a claimed range of 229 miles.

So is the Inster the must-have small EV? Or would you choose the EC3 instead? Let us know in the comments!

About The Show:

Set in Lucknow the show is based in one such all-women Police station made by 4 beautiful quirky women. Pushpa, the oldest of them, is the head constable who tries to balance her life between home and work. Karishma, the Sub Inspector, is fish out of the water as she is at loggerheads with the philosophy of the police station. She beats before she talks but now she has to solve all cases through reconciliation. Santosh Sharma is a young new recruit and a typical lonely girl in the city. Description:
If you see your cat fighting with a large snake, don't panic; your cat has no chance of losing this encounter.
That's because snakes, which are a nightmare for humans and many other creatures, are helpless when faced with cats.
The reason is that while a cat's average reaction time is between 20 and 70 milliseconds, for snakes, it's between 44 and 70 milliseconds.
Snakes can only use this speed and reaction time when striking or pulling their heads back, while cats can move their paws, heads, spines, necks, and entire bodies at this speed.
On top of that, when we add cats' predatory instincts, they become a snake's worst nightmare. That's why, in villages and farms, people keep cats not just for mice but also for snakes. #animals #animalshorts #catsreaction #catshorts

After two decades as one of the most beloved and enduring musicals on the stage, Wicked makes its long-awaited journey to the big screen as a spectacular, generation-defining cinematic event this holiday season. 

Wicked, the untold story of the witches of Oz, stars Emmy, Grammy and Tony winning powerhouse Cynthia Erivo (Harriet, Broadway‚Äôs The Color Purple) as Elphaba, a young woman, misunderstood because of her unusual green skin, who has yet to discover her true power, and Grammy-winning, multi-platinum recording artist and global superstar Ariana Grande as Glinda, a popular young woman, gilded by privilege and ambition, who has yet to discover her true heart. 
 
The two meet as students at Shiz University in the fantastical Land of Oz and forge an unlikely but profound friendship. Following an encounter with The Wonderful Wizard of Oz, their friendship reaches a crossroads and their lives take very different paths. Glinda's unflinching desire for popularity sees her seduced by power, while Elphaba's determination to remain true to herself, and to those around her, will have unexpected and shocking consequences on her future. Their extraordinary adventures in Oz will ultimately see them fulfill their destinies as Glinda the Good and the Wicked Witch of the West. 
 
The film also stars Oscar¬Æ winner Michelle Yeoh as Shiz University‚Äôs regal headmistress Madame Morrible; Jonathan Bailey (Bridgerton, Fellow Travelers) as Fiyero, a roguish and carefree prince; Tony nominee Ethan Slater (Broadway‚Äôs Spongebob Squarepants, Fosse/Verdon) as Boq, an altruistic Munchkin student; Marissa Bode in her feature-film debut as Nessarose, Elphaba‚Äôs favored sister; and pop culture icon Jeff Goldblum as the legendary Wizard of Oz.
 
The cast of characters includes Pfannee and ShenShen, two conniving compatriots of Glinda played by Emmy nominee Bowen Yang (Saturday Night Live) and Bronwyn James (Harlots), and a new character created for the film, Miss Coddle, played by Tony nominee Keala Settle (The Greatest Showman). 
 
Directed by acclaimed filmmaker Jon M. Chu (Crazy Rich Asians, In the Heights), Wicked is the first chapter of a two-part immersive, cultural celebration. Wicked Part Two is scheduled to arrive in theaters on November 26, 2025.
 
Wicked is produced by Marc Platt (La La Land, The Little Mermaid), whose films, television shows and stage productions have earned a combined 46 Oscar¬Æ nominations, 58 Emmy nominations and 36 Tony nominations, and by multiple Tony winner David Stone (Kimberly Akimbo, Next to Normal), with whom Platt produced the blockbuster Wicked stage musical. The executive producers are David Nicksay, Stephen Schwartz and Jared LeBoff. 
 
Based on the bestselling novel by Gregory Maguire, Wicked is adapted for the screen by the stage production‚Äôs book writer Winnie Holzman and by legendary Grammy and Oscar¬Æ winning composer and lyricist Stephen Schwartz. The Broadway stage musical is produced by Universal Stage Productions, Marc Platt, the Araca Group, Jon B. Platt and David Stone.

Title: New Dacia Duster Review: The KING of Small SUVs?
Description:
Change your car with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Change-Your-Car-3010

This is the all-new Dacia Duster! 

It‚Äôs one of the cheapest SUVs money can buy, with the price starting from just ¬£18,000! The question is, even with such a low price tag, does it offer enough to compete with small SUV competitors like the Peugeot 2008? 

Well, when it comes to the design, the Duster has been heavily updated compared to the previous edition - and it looks fantastic! At the front, it looks so much more modern than the previous car, helping it look more desirable compared to some key competitors. Along the side there‚Äôs cladding around the wheel arches to give it a rugged look, and the roof bars and blacked-out windows only help improve the looks further. In conclusion, it‚Äôs fair to say that the Duster looks much better than you would expect an ¬£18,000 car to look! 

Step inside and the interior is pretty well laid out. The infotainment screen display may not be the best, but it offers all the functionality you need, including the ability to use Apple CarPlay & Android Auto. There are physical buttons for the climate control, and everything is pretty well laid out throughout the cabin. Unfortunately, though, the visibility to the outside isn‚Äôt as good as the previous edition, although it‚Äôs still more than liveable.

One key difference when it comes to the engines is the removal of the diesel option. As a result, there are now two petrol options - a 1.2-litre turbo that produces 130hp, and a 1.6-litre self-charging hybrid that can produce 140hp. 

So is the Duster still the best budget SUV around? Or should you look elsewhere instead? Stick with Mat to see for yourself!

Singham (Ajay Devgn) takes on Corrupt Officer and Politician | Action-packed Movie Clip
Description:
Singham (Ajay Devgn) takes on Corrupt Officer and Politician | Action-packed Movie Clip
Inspector Rakesh Kadam (Sudhanshu Pandey) is an honest police officer who ends up committing suicide due to the false accusations of corruption levelled against him by Jaikant Shikre (Prakash Raj), a crime boss, businessman and politician in Goa running various rackets like kidnapping, extortion and smuggling. Kadam's wife Megha (Sonali Kulkarni) vows revenge against Jaikant in front of him, exclaiming that God will dispense justice to him for this act.

The story moves to Shivgad, a small village near the Goa-Maharashtra border. Bajirao Singham (Ajay Devgn), an honest police officer like Kadam, is in charge of the Shivgad police station. A station house officer in charge of his town, he resolves most of the problems in his town informally and without filing charge sheets, thereby gaining much reputation and love from the villagers. Gautam "Gotya" Bhosle (Sachin Khedekar) is an industrialist and Bajirao's father Manikrao "Manya" Singham's (Govind Namdev) childhood friend. He comes to Shivgad with his wife and daughters Kavya (Kajal Aggarwal) and Anjali (Sana Amin Sheikh). Eventually, Singham and Kavya fall in love with each other. Their courtship takes place through a series of comic events where she initially hates him after he slaps her tight when she is caught frightening villagers disguised as a ghost, but then has a change of heart when she sees his honest and simple nature and finds that he wants to apologize for his behaviour.

Everything seems to run smoothly until Jaikant, who is given conditional bail for a murdeer he had committed, is required to travel to Shivgad to sign the bail through a fortnight. Acting on the recommendation of his top lieutenant Shiva Naik (Ashok Samarth), he instead sends one of his allies, VOn the highway, as he stops at a point, he recalls his humiliation, learns of Singham's background from Shiva through a source, and using his political contacts, gets Singham transferred to Goa to seek revenge.

Singham, unaware of Jaikant's hand behind his transfer, joins the Colva police station in Goa as the in-charge, when on the very first day, he is confronted by Jaikant, who shows Singham his true colours and tries to intimidate him by mentioning how the officer preceding him ended up committing suicide, warning Singham that he is out to trouble him to no end. Feeling defeated and mentally tortured by Jaikant to no limits, a worried Singham first contemplates returning home but is stopped by Kavya, who encourages him to fight against the evil and not run away like a coward. At that point, some of Jaikant's henchmen attack him, and he, realizing the futility of returning to Shivgad, brutally beats the goons black and blue, locking them up.

Singham then arrests Shiva in a fake case of illegally smuggling alcohol after setting him up to tear the FIR against the goons, who he had come to free, and recalling to the officers that Shiva, under Jaikant's orders, had planted bundles of cash in Kadam's jeep.Rescuing her, Singham successfully traces the origins of the kidnapping racket to Jaikant, confronting Narvekar with his team in anger, but is unable to arrest him as he wins the election and is set to become a minister of the Goa Government.

Jaikant's party wins the elections, he hands over transfer orders to Singham to go back to Shivgad within 24 hours. That night, at a police function organized for the officers with their families, Singham confronts the officers, particularly Pawar and Patkar, for not abiding by their duties and being dishonest and unfaithful to their profession by protecting Jaikant.  They bring him to the police station and sh00t him de@d on Kadam's chair, threatening Shiva moments after the showdown to change his statement. At a media conference, while proving Jaikant and Narvekar guilty, Pawar and Singham clear the late Kadam of all corruption charges.

The film ends with Singham and the other police officers saluting Megha.

Title: New Renault Clio Review: Pay Less, Get MORE?!
Description:
Change your car with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Change-Your-Car-2810

This is the new Renault Clio! 

Renault‚Äôs supermini has received a mid-life facelift, and Mat‚Äôs going to put it through its paces to see if it can compete with class leaders like the Volkswagen Polo! 

In terms of the design, given that it‚Äôs only a mid-life facelift, it‚Äôs no surprise that it looks relatively similar to the previous edition. There‚Äôs an updated bumper at the front of the car, some new DLRs and updated headlights. These now come as LEDs as standard in all versions of this car! Along the side, the looks are almost identical, while the range-topping edition we have here has black window surrounds, which aren‚Äôt available on all trim levels. At the back, there‚Äôs a new bumper, as well as updated taillights. 

Step inside and the Clio is very much what you‚Äôd expect from a car in this class. There are some soft-touch materials on the dash, although this becomes scratchy black plastic lower down in the cabin. The edition we have here comes with comfortable sports seats, and there‚Äôs also a relatively large infotainment screen and a set of digital dials. Although the infotainment screen is relatively large, it doesn‚Äôt run Renault‚Äôs latest infotainment system, so it looks a bit old and can be quite laggy. 

There are two engines to choose from. The entry-level is a 1-litre 3-cylinder turbo petrol that can deliver 90hp, while the second option is a 1.6-litre self-charging hybrid that produces 145hp. 

In terms of the price, the Clio can undercut the majority of its competitors. The entry-level car costs ¬£18,000, 1.6-litre car costs ¬£21,600. The former is only available as a manual, while the latter has an automatic gearbox. In fact, the fully-specced range-topper (that we have for this video) only costs ¬£25,000! 

So is the Clio the smart choice for anyone choosing a new supermini? Or is a Polo or Fabia a better choice? Stick with Mat and see for yourself!

Race Car vs. Road Car! We race the Cadillac V-Series.R (LMDh) versus the Ferrari 296 GTB with Asseto Fiorano package, the McLaren 750S, and the Porsche 911 Turbo S (992.1) through the 1/4 mile ‚Äî including a roll race!

=
This episode is presented by Valentine One Radar Locator: Find radar before it finds you https://bit.ly/Valentine1_Hagerty

Click here to join the Hagerty Driver's Club: https://bit.ly/Join-HDC-Cammisa-UDRR
=

In this video, we perform instrumented 0-to-60 and quarter-mile testing on Cadillac's 2024 Le Mans entry, the Cadillac V-Series.R ‚Äî and race it against several roadgoing supercars.

Thanks to Balance of Performance (BOP) rules, the Cadillac's 5.5-liter cross plane-crank, 8800-rpm V-8 is limited in output thanks to a restrictor plate ‚Äî and its electric hybrid motor is also turned down.

But there are no BOP rules on the road, so the Cadillac team turned the wick all the way up.

Meanwhile, the road cars were vying for a chance to race the Cadillac. The Ferrari 296 GTB with Assetto Fiorano (sport) package comes with Michelin Pilot Cup 2R tires to deal with the 818 hp from its twin-turbo, 120¬∫ 3-liter V-6 and electric motors. 

The McLaren 720S uses a twin-turbocharged 4.0-liter flat-plane-crank V8. 

And the rear-engined Porsche 911 sends its 3.7-liter twin-turbo flat-six's power to all four wheels, with a blazing launch that'll keep up with a 1500-hp Bugatti Chiron Pur Sport to 60 mph.

But can any of them keep up with a Le Mans car? And what about in a rolling race from the Cadillac's 60-kph pit-speed limiter? We find out with Le Mans royalty S√©bastien Bourdais at the wheel!

Title: CAN'T LAND THE PLANE! -  Jet Airways 555's Insane Story
Description:
Let our sponsor BetterHelp connect you to a therapist who can support you - all from the comfort of your own home. Visit https://betterhelp.com/wyngx and enjoy a special discount on your first month.

On August 18, 2015, #jetairways 555, a #boeing 737-800 departed #Hamad International Airport in #Doha to Cochin in the Southern #indian state of #Kerala.  Although the initial weather was good, the forecast changed on their way. In this post-pandemic world, it is safe to assume that everyone, including your students, has experienced trauma in some form.

The FACT takes childhood trauma testing a step further to determine not if your student has experienced trauma, but to measure how trauma is impacting their academic and social-emotional growth in a classroom environment. Title: Koenigsegg v Model X Plaid: DRAG RACE
Description:

The Koenigsegg Agera RST is BACK! And it‚Äôs going up against the Tesla Model X Plaid! 

This is set to be one really interested drag race. We know the electric power of the Model X will propel it off the line, but not only is it down on power compared to the Koenigsegg, it‚Äôs also SO much heavier! But will that prove decisive? 

For starters, let‚Äôs check the stats. The Koenigsegg is powered by a 5-litre twin-turbo V8 that can produce 1,360hp and 1,570Nm of torque. This power is sent to the rear wheels only via a 7-speed dual-clutch gearbox, and the car weighs just 1,395kg. It‚Äôs one of the most expensive cars we‚Äôve ever featured, valued at a cool ¬£3,500,000!!

As for the Tesla, it‚Äôs powered by 3 electric motors, and these combine to produce 1,020hp and 1,420Nm. The car has all wheel drive, and it weighs in at a fairly colossal 2,468kg. If you‚Äôre looking to pick one up today, it‚Äôll cost around ¬£127,000. 

So the Tesla weighs over a tonne more than the Koenigsegg! So does it stand a chance? There‚Äôs only one way to find out‚Ä¶ LET‚ÄôS RACE!

Why are so many US states split in two? ü§îüá∫üá∏ #shorts
Description:
Why are so many US states split in two?

Transcript:  You got two different Carolinas, two Virginias, and two Dakotas, so, what's the reason for all these stats dividing? Well, for two of these cases, the answer is pretty straightforward.

For example, North Carolina and South Carolina were both once part of the British territory of Carolina, and mutually agreed to split mainly because of differing economic focuses.
Similarly, both North and South Dakota were once part of the large Dakota Territory, and split up for the simple reason that splitting into two states would allow for more representation in congress than if they had stayed together.

However, when it comes to why Virginia and West Virginia are two different states, the answer becomes a little more interesting. You see, instead of a territory simply being carved up, this split actually resulted from West Virginia forcefully seceding from Virginia. 

And to understand why, we need to go back to the early 1860s, when, nearing the beginning of the civil war, Virginia broke away from the Northern US to join the Confederate States of the South. However, many people in the northwest of Virginia were still loyal to the Union, so they severed ties with the rest of the state, and were admitted to the union as a brand new one. Although, because of their shared history, they decided to keep the same name.

Title: I CLONED a car and SOLD it!
Description:
Change your car with Carwow: https://bit.ly/Change-Your-Car-2410

Cloned cars are a serious issue in the UK. Some reports say there may be as many as 20,000 cloned cars on UK streets, while other reports say the number may be much higher! 

To get to the bottom of how criminals do this, Mat‚Äôs turned to the dark side and is going to attempt to clone a car himself! 

We‚Äôve picked up a second-hand Mk6 Golf for just ¬£500. It was so cheap because it‚Äôs received some damage, so it‚Äôs listed as a CAT N write-off, meaning it‚Äôs received some non-structural damage which is repairable. Mat's now going to follow in a proper criminal‚Äôs steps by attempting to pass this car as another Mk6 Golf (which is in better condition, of course) and try and sell it on for a profit! 

We‚Äôve enlisted the help of the RAC and Devon & Cornwall Police to see what steps criminals take to clone a car, and we‚Äôll also share some tips on how you can make sure you don‚Äôt buy a cloned car yourself. 

Have you ever been the victim of a cloned car? Let us know in the comments!

...................................................................................................

Carwow would like to thank the following individuals and organisations for their help with this video:

Owen Messenger and the Road Casualty Reduction Team, Devon and Cornwall Police
Simon Williams and the RAC ‚Äì https://www.rac.co.uk/drive
Chris Sutherland from Sutherland Car Care ‚Äì https://sutherlandplates.co.uk/
The National Police Chiefs‚Äô Council ‚Äì https://www.npcc.police.uk/
The DVLA ‚Äì https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/driver-and-vehicle-licensing-agency
CAP HPI ‚Äì https://www.hpi.co.uk/

For further information relating to vehicle cloning, including official guidance on what to do if you suspect your car has been cloned, download the Government‚Äôs DVLA Vehicle Registration Numbers and number plates advice booklet: 
https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/327622/INF104_230913.pdf

If you suspect a car has been cloned, contact your local police force ‚Äì many have dedicated online reporting services for incidents relating to car cloning. If you aren‚Äôt sure which police force serves your area, you can search by postcode here: 
https://www.police.uk/pu/find-a-police-force/

Carwow does not condone or encourage any of the activities or topics discussed in this video. This content is created solely for educational purposes and in the public interest to help viewers avoid becoming victims of such crimes. All driving scenes featuring incorrect registration plates were filmed on private land with the explicit consent of the landowner. We own both the vehicles featured in the video, at no point did we order registration plates for a car we do not own.¬† Additionally, all individuals appearing in this video have provided their consent to be filmed.

WHAT IS A HOME WARRANTY?
A home warranty is a year-long, renewable home service plan that helps with the cost to repair or replace parts of a home‚Äôs systems and appliances. Home warranties can also be referred to as home warranty policies, home warranty insurance, or home protection plans. It‚Äôs not homeowners insurance, but acts as a complement to it ‚Äì protecting things that your insurance doesn‚Äôt. 

Your home systems and appliances, like your water heater and oven, will break down over time. And sometimes, things just stop working, no matter how old they are. It happens. That‚Äôs where a home warranty comes in ‚Äì offering a budget-friendly solution for covered household breakdowns.

And if it‚Äôs peace of mind and convenience you‚Äôre looking for, we‚Äôve got you covered. Our service plans remove the guesswork. No time spent asking for repair recommendations or calling contractor after contractor. When things go wrong in your home, you‚Äôll know exactly what to do. 

WHAT IS COVERED IN A HOME WARRANTY?
We help protect major parts of your home systems and appliances, no matter their age, no maintenance records or home inspections required. It's similar to appliance insurance or system‚Äôs insurance that you may have for one item, but our home warranties help cover multiple items. Depending on the type of warranty you choose, we cover components of home systems, appliances, or both ‚Äì things like your heating system, water heater, electrical system, dishwasher, clothes washer/dryer, and more.

And if we can‚Äôt repair a covered item, we‚Äôll replace it. As a member, we want you to know that your budget, your time, and, let‚Äôs be honest, your sanity is all good.

Importance of Laxmi Mata : 
Goddess Lakshmi is the Hindu goddess of wealth, fortune and prosperity (both material and spiritual). Her name is derived from the Sanskrit word ‚ÄòLakshya‚Äô, which means aim or goal. 
She is the wife and Shakti (energy) of Vishnu, one of the principal deities of Hinduism and the Supreme Being in the Vaishnavism Tradition. Lakshmi is also an important deity in Jainism as well as Buddhism. 

Lakshmi is also called 'Sri' or 'Thirumagal' because she is endowed with six auspicious and divine qualities, or gunas, and is the divine strength of Vishnu. 

In Hindu religion, she was born from the churning of the 'Samudra Manthan' and she chose Vishnu as her eternal consort. When Vishnu descended on the Earth as the avatars Rama and Krishna, Lakshmi descended as his respective consort. The marriage and relationship between Lakshmi and Vishnu as wife and husband is the paradigm for rituals and ceremonies for the bride and groom in Hindu weddings.

Lakshmi is depicted in Indian art as an elegantly dressed, prosperity-showering golden-coloured woman with an owl as her vehicle, signifying the importance of economic activity in the maintenance of life, her ability to move, work and prevail in confusing darkness. 

She is often depicted as part of the Trinity (Tridevi) consisting of Saraswati, Lakshmi and Parvati.
The festivals of Diwali and Sharad Purnima (Kojagiri Purnima) are celebrated in her honour.

Benefits of Performing Maa Lakshmi Aarti :

Lakshmi Aarti is majorly done on Diwali, office/ house-warmings to take the blessings of the goddess of Wealth, Luxury and Prosperity. The Hindu culture strongly believes that Goddess Lakshmi Provides one with financial wellbeing and material gains.
